      a href="http://www.elasticsearch.org/guide/reference/api/admin-indices-aliases/" target="_blank" Aliases

  tr
    td
      code Elastics.post_index_aliases
    td
      markdown:
        The index aliases API allow to alias an index with a name, with all APIs automatically converting the alias name to the actual index name.

        **Template**

      |
        {% shighlight yaml %}
        post_index_aliases:
        - POST
        - /_aliases
        - actions: <<actions>>
        {% endshighlight %}

      markdown:
        **Usage**

      |
        {% shighlight ruby %}
        Elastics.post_index_aliases :actions => actions
        {% endshighlight %}

  tr
    td
      code Elastics.get_index_aliases
    td
      markdown:
        Returns all indices with all aliases, or just for specific indices. (pre 0.90.1).

        **Template**

      |
        {% shighlight yaml %}
        get_index_aliases:
        - GET
        - /<<index>>/_aliases
        {% endshighlight %}

      markdown:
        **Usage**

      |
        {% shighlight ruby %}
        Elastics.get_index_aliases :index => "elastics_test_index"
        {% endshighlight %}



  tr
    td
      code Elastics.add_index_alias
    td
      markdown:
        Adds an index alias.

        **Template**

      |
        {% shighlight yaml %}
        add_index_alias:
        - PUT
